    },
    {
      "source_kind": "repo-description",
      "source_repo": "ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "\ud83d\ude43   A delightful community-driven (with 2,400+ contributors) framework for managing your zsh configuration. Includes 300+ optional plugins (rails, git, macOS, hub, docker, homebrew, node, php, python, etc), 140+ themes to spice up your morning, and an auto-update tool that makes it easy to keep up with the latest updates from the community."
    },
    {
      "source_kind": "source-snippet",
      "source_repo": "ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://ohmyzsh.s3.amazonaws.com/omz-ansi-github.png\" alt=\"Oh My Zsh\"></p>"
    },
    {
      "source_kind": "repo-description",
      "source_repo": "oh-my-fish/oh-my-fish",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "The Fish Shell Framework"
    },
    {
      "source_kind": "source-snippet",
      "source_repo": "oh-my-fish/oh-my-fish",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "> \u26a0\ufe0f Oh My Fish has been unmaintained for years, and certain parts of it may not work for you. A few themes and packages are currently broken, and the code is due a significant overhaul. The current set of maintainers have ran out of steam, so if you are interested in becoming a\u2026"
    },
    {
      "source_kind": "repo-description",
      "source_repo": "unixorn/awesome-zsh-plugins",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "A collection of ZSH frameworks, plugins, themes and tutorials."
    },
    {
      "source_kind": "source-snippet",
      "source_repo": "unixorn/awesome-zsh-plugins",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "[![Awesome](https://awesome.re/badge.svg)](https://awesome.re)"
    },
    {
      "source_kind": "repo-description",
      "source_repo": "unixorn/zsh-quickstart-kit",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "A simple ZSH quickstart for using ZSH, zgenom, oh-my-zsh and a curated list of extra plugins. It is designed to be easy to customize without requiring you to maintain your own fork."
